status: MARC21-007: Color characteristics of a motion picture
Color characteristics of a motion picture.

definition (en): Printed or executed in more than one color.
Motion picture, produced by a printing or photographic process, is hand colored.
scope note (en): Rarely used with commercial films since these are not typically issued with hand coloring.

definition (en): Work or collection is a combination of black-and-white, multicolored, hand colored, and/or other images.
Color characteristics are not applicable because the item has no images.
scope note (en): Used, for example, when the item in hand is sound track film intended to accompany visual images not actually present.

definition (en): Color characteristics of the motion picture are not known.
Color other than black-and-white, multicolored, hand colored, mixed.
